rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: This opcode has similar semantics to `CALLDATACOPY`, but instead of copying data from the call data, it copies data from the return data buffer. Furthermore, accessing the return data buffer beyond its size results in a failure, i.e. if `start + length` overflows or results in a value larger than `RETURNDATASIZE`, the current call stops in an out-of-gas condition.
